3921#article=6017MEIwNUQwRUY5RjVFNTI2RDk2NTVDQUQyRTY4N0U2RTQ=|title=Israeli pro basketball player comes out as bisexual}}</ref>\n* [[Tzipora Obziler]], tennis player<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.outsports.com/2012/7/26/4053450/over-100-out-lgbt-athletes-have-competed-in-the-summer-olympics|title=Over 100 out LGBT athletes have competed in the Summer Olympics|last=Zeigler|first=Cyd|date=2012-07-26|website=Outsports|access-date=2019-02-20}}</ref>\n* [[Ren\u00e9e Richards]], tennis player<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=7277665|title=The Second Half of My Life}}</ref>\n* [[Sue Bird]], American-Israeli<ref>[https://forward.com/news/israel/160992/sue-bird-first-israeli-to-win-gold/ Sue Bird First Israeli To Win Gold \u2013 The Forward<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> basketball player who has won three [[List of WNBA champions|WNBA championships]] ([[2004 WNBA Finals|2004]], [[2010 WNBA Finals|2010]], [[2018 WNBA Finals|2018]]), four [[Basketball at the Summer Olympics|Olympic gold medals]], ([[Basketball at the 2004 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's team squads|2004]], [[Basketball at the 2008 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's team rosters|2008]], [[Basketball at the 2012 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's team rosters|2012]], [[Basketball at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's team rosters|2016]]), two NCAA Championships (2000 and 2002), and four [[FIBA World Cup]]s (2002, 2010, 2014, and 2018)\n\n==Miscellaneous==\n*[[Gad Beck]], Holocaust survivor and memoirist<ref>[http://www.ushmm.org/wlc/idcard.php?lang=en&ModuleId=10006666 Gad Beck<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090506090817/http://www.ushmm.org/wlc/idcard.php?lang=en&ModuleId=10006666 |date=2009-05-06 }}</ref>\n* [[Barbara Brenner]], breast cancer activist and leader of [[Breast Cancer Action]]<ref>Sjoholm, Barbara (Editor) (2016). ''So Much To Be Done: The Writings of Breast Cancer Activist Barbara Brenner''. [[University of Min