uthor, and assistant rabbi and music director at Congregation Beth El<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bethelberkeley.org|title=bethelberkeley.org -|website=www.bethelberkeley.org}}</ref> in [[Berkeley, California]];<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.transtorah.org/whoweare.html |title=> Who We Are |publisher=TransTorah |date= |accessdate=2013-10-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jweekly.com/article/full/58262/the-early-shift-bimah-bound-a-transformative-experience/ |title=The early shift, Bimah-bound, A transformative experience &#124; j. the Jewish news weekly of Northern California |publisher=Jweekly.com |date=2010-06-03 |accessdate=2013-10-13}}</ref> first openly transgender person accepted to the Reform Jewish seminary [[Hebrew Union College-Jewish Institute of Religion]] in [[Cincinnati]] (2003);<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jewishjournal.com/world/article/world_briefs_20030321/ |title=World Briefs &#124; World |publisher=Jewish Journal |date=2003-03-20 |accessdate=2013-10-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jweekly.com/article/full/33139/blessed-are-the-transgendered-say-s-f-rabbi-and-the-reform-movement/ |title=Blessed are the transgendered, say S.F. rabbi and the Reform movement &#124; j. the Jewish news weekly of Northern California |publisher=Jweekly.com |date=2007-08-17 |accessdate=2013-10-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://forward.com/articles/11403/reform-devises-sex-change-blessings-/ |title=Reform Devises Sex-Change Blessings \u2013 |publisher=Forward.com |date= |accessdate=2013-10-13}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=ryGT9ZMBi4cC&pg=PA193&dq=%22Reuben+Zellman%22#v=onepage&q=%22Reuben%20Zellman%22&f=false |title=Imagining Holiness: Classic Hasidic Tales in Modern Times - Justin Jaron Lewis - Google Books |date= June 2009|accessdate=2013-10-13|isbn=9780773535190 |last1=Lewis |first1=Justin Jaron }}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=rQ-21kefOC4C&pg=PT175&dq=%22Reuben+Zellman%22#v=onepage&q=%22Reuben%2