, Stephen (June 2004), [https://www.wired.com/wired/archive/12.06/blog.html How Can I Sex Up This Blog Business?], Wired.com. Retrieved November 18, 2006.</ref>\n* [[Joel Derfner]], writer and memoirist<ref name=joelderfner />\n*[[Gaby Dunn]], writer, journalist, comedian, and actress<ref>[http://gabydunn.com/about%3E%3E literature >>Gaby Dunn<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20061210155033/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2VFFbpC96R4|date=December 10, 2006}}</ref>\n* [[Elana Dykewomon]], American novelist<ref>{{cite web|title=What Can I Ask by Elana Dykewomon|url=http://awiderbridge.org/what-can-i-ask-by-elana-dykewomon/|website=A Wider Bridge: Building LGBTQ Connections with Israel|publisher=A Wider Bridge|date=2015-11-05|accessdate=2016-03-12}}</ref>\n* Shiri Eisner, Israeli activist, writer, blogger, and researcher<ref name=\"Yadid\">{{cite news|url=http://www.haaretz.com/israel-news/travel/gay-tel-aviv/tel-aviv-pride/.premium-1.598005|title=Power and Pride: 7 Queer Jews to be Reckoned With|last=Yadid|first=Judd|work=Haaretz|date=2014-06-10|accessdate=2016-03-15}}</ref>\n* [[Gy\u00f6rgy Faludy]], poet<ref>{{cite news|url=http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m2242/is_1656_284/ai_n6141789 |title=Gyorgy Faludy: the passions of Hungary's controversial poet |first=Thomas |last=Orszag-Land |year=2004 |work=Contemporary Review |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060616084707/http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m2242/is_1656_284/ai_n6141789 |archivedate=2006-06-16 }}</ref>\n* [[Leslie Feinberg]], activist, author <ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.advocate.com/arts-entertainment/books/2014/11/17/transgender-pioneer-leslie-feinberg-stone-butch-blues-has-died/|title=Transgender Pioneer and ''Stone Butch Blues'' Author Leslie Feinberg Has Died|work=The Advocate|date=2014-11-17|accessdate=2016-03-12}}</ref>\n* [[Edward Field (poet)|Edward Field]], poet<ref>[http://www.glbtq.com/literature/field_e.html glbtq >> l