87/format/html/displaystory.html|title=j. - Novelist examines converging worlds of Jews and gays<!-- Bot generated title -->}}</ref>\n* [[Jay Michaelson]],<ref>{{cite web|last=Ring |first=Trudy |url=http://www.advocate.com/news/news-features/2012/04/06/easter-treat-christians-your-side?page=0,4 |title=An Easter Treat Christians on Your Side |publisher=Advocate.com |date=2012-04-06 |accessdate=2013-11-19}}</ref> writer, columnist, author of ''God vs. Gay?''<ref>{{Cite book |title=God vs. Gay?: The Religious Case for Equality (Queer Action / Queer Ideas): Jay Michaelson: 9780807001479: Amazon.com: Books |date=2012-05-08 |isbn=978-0807001479 |url-access=registration |url=https://archive.org/details/godvsgay_mich_2011_000_10771136 }}</ref>\n* [[Herbert Muschamp]] <ref>{{cite web|url=http://search.barnesandnoble.com/Hearts-of-the-City/Herbert-Muschamp/e/9780375404061#EXC|title=Hearts of the City|first=Barnes &|last=Noble|website=Barnes & Noble}}</ref> (1947\u20132007), ''[[New York Times]]'' architecture critic\n* [[Leslea Newman]], children's book author, short story writer, editor <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.keshetonline.org/product/leslea-newman-lgbt-jewish-heroes-poster/|title=Keshet: Leslean Newman Poster|publisher=Keshet|accessdate=2016-03-12}}</ref>\n* [[Harold Norse]], poet<ref>[http://www.glbtq.com/literature/norse_h.html glbtq >> literature >> Norse, Harold<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20061019233101/http://www.glbtq.com/literature/norse_h.html |date=2006-10-19 }}</ref>\n* [[Marcel Proust]], novelist <ref>[http://www.glbtq.com/literature/proust_m.html glbtq >> literature >> Proust, Marcel<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070211134328/http://www.glbtq.com/literature/proust_m.html |date=February 11, 2007 }}</ref>\n* [[David Rakoff]],  essayist<ref>[http://archive.salon.com/people/conv/2001/06/11/rakoff/index.html Salon.com People | David Rakoff<!-- Bot generated title -->]