04]], [[2010 WNBA Finals|2010]], [[2018 WNBA Finals|2018]]), four [[Basketball at the Summer Olympics|Olympic gold medals]], ([[Basketball at the 2004 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's team squads|2004]], [[Basketball at the 2008 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's team rosters|2008]], [[Basketball at the 2012 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's team rosters|2012]], [[Basketball at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's team rosters|2016]]), two NCAA Championships (2000 and 2002), and four [[FIBA World Cup]]s (2002, 2010, 2014, and 2018)\n\n==Miscellaneous==\n*[[Gad Beck]], Holocaust survivor and memoirist<ref>[http://www.ushmm.org/wlc/idcard.php?lang=en&ModuleId=10006666 Gad Beck<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090506090817/http://www.ushmm.org/wlc/idcard.php?lang=en&ModuleId=10006666 |date=2009-05-06 }}</ref>\n* [[Barbara Brenner]], breast cancer activist and leader of [[Breast Cancer Action]]<ref>Sjoholm, Barbara (Editor) (2016). ''So Much To Be Done: The Writings of Breast Cancer Activist Barbara Brenner''. [[University of Minnesota]] Press, USA. {{ISBN|978-0-8166-9944-5}}</ref>\n* [[Roy Cohn]], lawyer and co-counsel (with [[Robert F. Kennedy]]) to Sen. [[Joseph McCarthy]]<ref>[http://www.glbtq.com/social-sciences/cohn_r.html glbtq >> social sciences >> Cohn, Roy<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20061208120354/http://www.glbtq.com/social-sciences/cohn_r.html |date=December 8, 2006 }}</ref>\n* [[Jonathan Danilowitz]], activist<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/justine-borer/being-gay-in-tel-aviv_b_4119275.html|title=Being Gay in Tel Aviv, the Manhattan of the Middle East|last=Borer|first=Justine|date=2013-10-18|website=Huffington Post|access-date=2019-02-20}}</ref>\n* [[Barry Diller]], media executive<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nymag.com/nymetro/urban/gay/features/4431/index.html|title=Inside Out|website=NYMag.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allbusiness.com/technology/648736-1.html|title=The Barry Diller Story, The Life and Times of America's Greatest Entertainment Mogul. - Construction > Residential Construction from AllBusiness.com<!-- Bot generated title -->}}</ref>\n* [[Sandi Simcha DuBowski]], documentary filmmaker<ref name=\"Austin\">{{cite news   | last = Lewis  | first = Anne S.  | title = Keeping the Faith: 'Trembling Before G-d' asks if coming out and staying in the Orthodox Jewish community is an impossible dream  | work =  | pages =  | publisher = Austin Chronicle  | date = 9 April 2002  | url = http://www.austinchronicle.com/gyrobase/Issue/story?oid=oid%3A85654  | accessdate = 2007-02-11}}</ref>\n* [[Brian Epstein]], manager of [[The Beatles]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/news/story/9226300/beatles_manager_subject_of_film|title=Music News \u2013 Rolling Stone|website=www.rollingstone.com}}</ref>\n* Israel David Fishman, founder of the Task Force on Gay Liberation, a section of the Social Responsibilities Round Table of the [[American Library Association]] (ALA), precursor of ALA's Gay Lesbian Bisexual Transgender Round Table <ref>{{cite web|url=http://archives.nypl.org/mss/1012|title=archives.nypl.org: Israel David Fishman Papers|publisher=New York Public Library Archives and Manuscripts|date=2016|accessdate=2016-03-15}}</ref>\n* [[Raffi Freedman-Gurspan]], first transgender person in the role of LGBT liaison to the White House <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.myjewishlearning.com/keshet/raffi-freedman-gurspan-the-white-houses-primary-lgbt-liaison/|title=Q&A with Raffi Freedman-Gurspan, the White House's Primary LGBT Liaison|last=Rozensky|first=Jordyn|date=2016-03-14|accessdate=2016-03-15}}</ref>\n* [[David Geffen]], film producer and record executive<ref>[http://www.glbtq.com/arts/geffen_d.html glbtq >> arts >> Geffen, David<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20061020002939/http://www.glbtq.com/arts/geffen_d.html |date=October 20, 2006 }}</ref>\n* [[Jazz Jennings]], transgender activist<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://reformjudaism.org/jewish-life/arts-culture/literature/being-jazz-my-life-transgender-teen|title=Being Jazz: My Life as a (Transgender) Teen|date=2016-07-06|work=ReformJudaism.org|access-date=2017-11-21}}</ref>\n*[[Frank Kameny]], prominent gay rights activist from 1957 to 2011 (born to Jewish parents but became an atheist)<ref>{{cite web |title=LGBT History Month: Frank Kameny {{!}} Human Rights Campaign |url=https://www.hrc.org/blog/lgbt-history-month-frank-kameny |website=[[Human Rights Campaign]] |accessdate=26 July 2018 }}</ref>\n* [[Eva Kotchever]], Polish feminist, owner of the [[Eve's Hangout]] in New York, assassinated at [[Auschwitz]]<ref name=Gattuso>{{cite web|last=Gattuso|first=Reina|url=http://www.atlasobscura.com/articles/what-was-first-gay-bar|title=The Founder of America's Earliest Lesbian Bar Was Deported for Obscenity|website=[[Atlas Obscura]]|date=September 3, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Miz Cracker]], American drag queen<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.haaretz.com/jewish/comic-and-contemplative-miz-cracker-is-the-fabulous-jewish-drag-queen-1.6174997|title=Comic and Contemplative, Miz Cracker Is the Fabulous Jewish Drag Queen We Need|last=Forward|first=The|date=2018-06-14|work=Haaretz|access-date=2019-02-20}}</ref>\n* [[Ezra Nawi]], Israeli human rights activist<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.haaretz.com/hasen/spages/1110755.html|title=Campaign seeks to keep rights activist out of prison |last=Levinson|first=Chaim|date=28 August 2009|publisher=Haaretz|accessdate=12 April 2010}}</ref>\n* [[Dana Olmert]], activist<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ynetnews.com/articles/0,7340,L-3327143,00.html|title=PM's daughter slams lack of support for gay parade|date=2006-12-11|website=Ynetnews|access-date=2019-02-20}}</ref>\n* [[Yotam Ottolenghi]], chef<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2013/aug/03/yotam-ottolenghi-gay-fatherhood-parenting|title=Yotam Ottolenghi: why I'm coming out as a gay father|last=Ottolenghi|first=Yotam|date=2013-08-03|work=The Guardian|access-date=2019-02-20|issn=0261-3077}}</ref>\n* [[Etai Pinkas]], activist<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ameinu.net/blog/israel/love-not-bombs-an-evening-with-etai-pinkas/|title=Love Not Bombs: An Evening with Etai Pinkas {{!}} Ameinu|access-date=2019-02-20}}</ref>\n*[[Felice Schragenheim]], Jewish resistance fighter and Holocaust victim<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.haaretz.com/life/books/.premium-gay-and-jewish-in-wartime-berlin-1.5315422|title=Gay and Jewish in Wartime Berlin: The Link Between Homosexuality and Zionism|last=Shapira|first=Avner|date=2013-08-02|work=Haaretz|access-date=2019-02-20}}</ref>\n*[[Ari Shapiro]], American radio journalist<ref>{{cite web|url=http://yaledailynews.com/blog/2004/03/05/yalies-walk-a-fine-line-down-the-aisle-in-san-francisco|title=Yalies walk a fine line down the aisle in San Francisco |last=Poppick|first=Susie|date=5 March 2004|publisher=Yale Daily News|accessdate=4 June 2013}}</ref>\n* [[Joel Simkhai]], [[Grindr]] founder and former CEO<ref name=\"Yadid\"/>\n* [[Randi Weingarten]], current president of the [[American Federation of Teachers]]<ref>Josh Nathan-Kazis. [http://www.forward.com/articles/127978/ \"The Leading Jew in Labor Wears Pearls\"], ''[[The Forward]]'', May 12, 2010, issue of May 21, 2010.</ref>\n* [[Riki Wilchins]], activist <ref>{{Cite book|title=Queer Theory, Gender Theory: An Instant Primer|last=Wilchins|first=Riki|oclc = 55078068}}</ref>\n* [[Ron Yosef]], activist<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.timeout.com/israel/blog/get-in-character-with-ron-yosef-orthodox-gay-activist-060417|title=Get in character with Ron Yosef, Orthodox Gay Activist|website=Time Out Israel|access-date=2019-02-20}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Homosexuality and Judaism]]\n*[[Keshet Rabbis]]\n*[[LGBT clergy in Judaism]]\n*[[Timeline of LGBT Jewish history]]\n\n==Footnotes==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.glbtjews.org World Congress of Gay & Le